File: Raindrops seen on a window. AFP/Tauseef Mustafa JOHANNESBURG -  It is a nightmare on Johannesburg roads. Rain pelted down as Eskom announced Stage 4 powercuts on Wednesday. READ: Help for affected Ivory Park residents following floods Traffic jams became the order of the day as a result of robots not working.   Some roads were also flooded. The commute to work and school saw traffic backed up at several intersections. Motorists are urged to exercise caution and keep a safe driving distance.